{% # Group v1.4.0 %}

{% comment %}
  Changelog
  - v1.4.0 — replace `bleed` boolean with responsive `bleed_desktop` (none/inline_start/inline_end/both) + `bleed_mobile` (none/both) enums. Emits `bleed-desktop:<value>` / `bleed-mobile:<value>` modifiers consumed by the section's named-line bleed grid (substrate `layer-theme.css` rewrite). Removes the snippet's own bleed CSS — section handles via `grid-column`. Per the subgrid migration (`.context/docs/subgrid-migration.md`); strict container-only bleed model.
  - v1.3.0 — rename BEM-style inner wrapper class `shopify-block--group__inner` to rscss-compliant `.inner` (scoped via `.shopify-block--group > .inner`). Restructure stylesheet to native nesting on the outer class. Per-project CSS targeting the old class name must rename.
  - v1.2.0 — read `container_style` metaobject and emit `container-style:<handle>` modifier when set. Centralized variant CSS (card / outlined / elevated) lives in `core.css` `@layer theme`.
  - v1.1.2 — emit `{{ block.shopify_attributes }}` on the root for theme-editor block selection (was missing)
  - v1.1.1 — route content_width + top-margin vars through `utility--block-layout-vars`; output unchanged
  - v1.1.0 — add `bleed` param emitted as `,bleed` modifier; CSS escapes the section gutter to the visible viewport width (same math as media's bleed)
  - v1.0.3 — normalize `horizontal_alignment: space-between` → `start` in column direction so the invalid `align-items: space-between` value doesn't fall through to the browser
  - v1.0.2 — wrap contents in `.shopify-block--group__inner`; container-type stays on the outer so `@container group` queries actually match (queries never see the element that defines the container per spec). Flex/stack-below rules move to the inner wrapper.
  - v1.0.1 — chain `--block-rhythm-mobile`/`--block-rhythm-desktop` as inner fallback for `margin-block-start` so section-level block rhythm applies when no per-block margin is authored
  - v1.0.0 — initial
{% endcomment %}

{% doc %}
  @description Renders a flex container that groups child blocks. Direction (column/row), alignment, gap, and breakpoint stacking are merchant-configurable. Stack-below uses `@container` queries against the group's own width (not the viewport), so a row-direction group placed inside a narrow column stacks correctly without false-positive matches against the viewport breakpoint.

  @param {section} [section] - The section object containing the block
  @param {block} [block] - Block object containing the settings
  @param {string} [block_id] - Unique block ID for static renders
  @param {string} [contents] - Pre-rendered child blocks markup. Skips render when blank.
  @param {string} [direction] - `'column'` (default) or `'row'`.
  @param {string} [stack_below] - In `row` direction, switch to column when container is below the breakpoint. One of `'none'`, `'40'`, `'60'`, `'80'` (rem). Defaults to `'60'`.
  @param {string} [horizontal_alignment] - In `column` direction maps to `align-items`; in `row` direction maps to `justify-content`. One of `'start'` (default), `'center'`, `'end'`, `'space-between'`.
  @param {string} [vertical_alignment] - In `row` direction maps to `align-items`. One of `'start'` (default), `'center'`, `'end'`. Ignored in `column` direction.
  @param {metaobject} [content_width] - `content_width` metaobject. Caps `max-inline-size`. Full width when blank. Composes with bleed (cap = section's content cap; per `container-patterns.md`).
  @param {number} [gap] - Gap between children in px. Defaults to 16.
  @param {string} [bleed_desktop] - At/above 48rem: extend the group's start / end / both edges to the section's bleed boundary. One of `'none'` (default), `'inline_start'`, `'inline_end'`, `'both'`. Emitted as `bleed-desktop:<value>` modifier when ≠ `none`; the section's named-line bleed grid handles positioning.
  @param {string} [bleed_mobile] - Below 48rem: full-bleed only. One of `'none'` (default) or `'both'`. Single-column mobile has no edge tracks, so per-side bleed has no geometric meaning there.
  @param {metaobject} [container_style] - `container_style` metaobject. Reads `.system.handle`; emits `container-style:<handle>` modifier. Centralized CSS in `layer-theme.css` handles card / outlined / elevated.
  @param {string} [color_scheme] - Optional `color_scheme` setting value. When set, emits `color-scheme:<id>` modifier so the global scheme rules from `utility--css-variables` apply.
  @param {number} [mobile_margin_block_start] - Top margin in px below the desktop breakpoint. Defaults to 0.
  @param {number} [desktop_margin_block_start] - Top margin in px at or above the desktop breakpoint. Defaults to 0.

  @example {% render 'group', section: section, block: block, contents: contents %}
{% enddoc %}

{% liquid
  assign direction = direction | default: block.settings.direction | default: 'column'
  assign stack_below = stack_below | default: block.settings.stack_below | default: '60'
  assign horizontal_alignment = horizontal_alignment | default: block.settings.horizontal_alignment | default: 'start'
  if direction == 'column' and horizontal_alignment == 'space-between'
    assign horizontal_alignment = 'start'
  endif
  assign vertical_alignment = vertical_alignment | default: block.settings.vertical_alignment | default: 'start'
  assign content_width = content_width | default: block.settings.content_width | default: ''
  assign gap = gap | default: block.settings.gap | default: 16
  assign bleed_desktop = bleed_desktop | default: block.settings.bleed_desktop | default: 'none'
  assign bleed_mobile = bleed_mobile | default: block.settings.bleed_mobile | default: 'none'
  assign container_style = container_style | default: block.settings.container_style | default: ''
  assign color_scheme = color_scheme | default: block.settings.color_scheme | default: ''
  assign mobile_margin_block_start = mobile_margin_block_start | default: block.settings.mobile_margin_block_start | default: 0
  assign desktop_margin_block_start = desktop_margin_block_start | default: block.settings.desktop_margin_block_start | default: 0

  assign modifier_list = 'direction:' | append: direction
  if direction == 'row' and stack_below != 'none'
    assign modifier_list = modifier_list | append: ',stack-below:' | append: stack_below
  endif
  if bleed_desktop != 'none'
    assign modifier_list = modifier_list | append: ',bleed-desktop:' | append: bleed_desktop
  endif
  if bleed_mobile != 'none'
    assign modifier_list = modifier_list | append: ',bleed-mobile:' | append: bleed_mobile
  endif
  if container_style != blank
    assign modifier_list = modifier_list | append: ',container-style:' | append: container_style.system.handle
  endif
  if color_scheme != blank
    assign modifier_list = modifier_list | append: ',color-scheme:' | append: color_scheme
  endif

  capture base_selector
    render 'utility--base-selector', section: section, block: block, identifier: block_id
  endcapture
  assign base_selector = base_selector | strip

  capture modifiers
    render 'utility--modifiers', modifier_list: modifier_list
  endcapture
%}

<div class="shopify-block shopify-block--group" id="{{ base_selector }}" {{ block.shopify_attributes }} {{ modifiers }}>
  <div class="inner">
    {{ contents }}
  </div>

  {% capture dynamic_style %}
    {% if gap and gap > 0 %}
      --gap: {{ gap | divided_by: 16.0 | round: 3 }}rem;
    {% endif %}

    {% if horizontal_alignment != 'start' %}
      --horizontal-alignment: {{ horizontal_alignment }};
    {% endif %}

    {% if vertical_alignment != 'start' %}
      --vertical-alignment: {{ vertical_alignment }};
    {% endif %}

    {% render 'utility--block-layout-vars', content_width: content_width, mobile_margin_block_start: mobile_margin_block_start, desktop_margin_block_start: desktop_margin_block_start %}
  {% endcapture %}
  {% render 'utility--dynamic-style', base_selector: base_selector, css_content: dynamic_style %}
</div>

{% stylesheet %}
  @layer components {
    /* Outer wrapper hosts the named container so descendant @container queries can match. The flex layout lives on .inner — querying the same element that defines the container never matches per spec. Bleed is now declared by the section's named-line grid (see `assets/layer-theme.css` and `.context/docs/subgrid-migration.md`); this snippet emits the bleed modifiers but does not own bleed CSS. */
    .shopify-block--group {
      container-type: inline-size;
      container-name: group;

      max-inline-size: var(--content-width, 100%);

      & > .inner {
        display: flex;
        gap: var(--gap, 0rem);
      }

      &[data-modifiers*='direction:column'] > .inner {
        flex-direction: column;
        align-items: var(--horizontal-alignment, start);
      }

      &[data-modifiers*='direction:row'] > .inner {
        flex-direction: row;
        justify-content: var(--horizontal-alignment, start);
        align-items: var(--vertical-alignment, start);
      }

      /* Stack-below: collapse to column when container is narrower than the breakpoint */
      &[data-modifiers*='stack-below'] > .inner {
        flex-direction: column;
        align-items: var(--horizontal-alignment, start);
      }
    }

    @container group (inline-size >= 40rem) {
      .shopify-block--group[data-modifiers*='stack-below:40'] > .inner {
        flex-direction: row;
        justify-content: var(--horizontal-alignment, start);
        align-items: var(--vertical-alignment, start);
      }
    }

    @container group (inline-size >= 60rem) {
      .shopify-block--group[data-modifiers*='stack-below:60'] > .inner {
        flex-direction: row;
        justify-content: var(--horizontal-alignment, start);
        align-items: var(--vertical-alignment, start);
      }
    }

    @container group (inline-size >= 80rem) {
      .shopify-block--group[data-modifiers*='stack-below:80'] > .inner {
        flex-direction: row;
        justify-content: var(--horizontal-alignment, start);
        align-items: var(--vertical-alignment, start);
      }
    }
  }
{% endstylesheet %}
